@begin(theorem)
A plain name renders as a div with that class.
@end(theorem)

@begin(pull-quote)
A hyphenated name renders as a custom element.
@end(pull-quote)

@begin(.side-bar)
The dot prefix forces a class even on a hyphenated name.
@end(.side-bar)

@begin(<aside>)[Note]{id="a"}
The angle-bracket wrapper forces an element on a plain name, with attrs and a label.
@end(<aside>)
